{center}
{subhead}Amiga running on RIORED{def}
{left}
{pp}
Silicon Fruit announced that AMIGA OS will be able to run on top of its RIORED
motherboard. The motherboard has 2 slot1 CPU slot for IBM PowerPC G3cx / 550 MHz,
IBM CPC 710 chipset, PCI (66 / 33 MHz), AGP, USB. The future version will use 700 MHz
CPU. Silicon Fruit said that virtually any operating system can be used on this hardware platform
(QNX, FreeBSD, NetBSD, BeOS, or even AmigaOS and MinT).
{pp}